    "created_at": "2016-07-21T23:50:44Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-07-21T23:50:44Z",
    "body": "I think the name of the method name is confusing and misleading because it doesn't actually control the zoom level limits, it controls the page scale limits. Zoom increases or decreases the size of elements on the page. Page scale changes the size of the viewport and doesn't distort the page layout like zoom can. `setDefaultPageScaleLimits` does indeed control the limits for pinching, but those are not the zoom limits. To control the zoom limits you have to call `zoomLimitsChanged`\n"
  },
